<![CDATA[<div style="text-align: right;"><div style=""><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" size="2" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;"><br></span></font></div><div style="text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.Salutation} {!Contact.LastName},</span></font></div><div style="text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><div style=""><br></div><div style="">Following the discovery of a small piece of metal on the football pitch at the weekend, I have asked the roofing contractors to come and conduct a survey of the roof.&nbsp; &nbsp;Initially they had hoped to complete the work today.&nbsp; &nbsp;I have however just spoken to them and they have requested another day to ensure that every part of the roof is checked very carefully and any further debris is found and removed.&nbsp; &nbsp;As the safety and wellbeing of students and&nbsp; staff is our top priority I have agreed to this.&nbsp;</div><div style=""><br></div><div style="">Unfortunately it does mean that the planned Sports Days for KS2 and Secondary tomorrow will need to be rescheduled into the week after Half term.&nbsp; &nbsp;Whilst it is frustrating to have to close the facilities at short notice and to postpone calendared events (and I do understand&nbsp; the inconvenience this may have caused in terms of people having already&nbsp; agreed&nbsp; time off to attend&nbsp; and support these events),&nbsp;your children's safety is paramount and this work can only be done in full daylight.&nbsp; &nbsp;</div><div style=""><br></div><div style="">My apologies once again for the change of plan.&nbsp; &nbsp;I do though&nbsp; look forward to seeing many of you cheering on our students when we hold the Sports Days on Wednesday 19th February.&nbsp;</div><div style=""><br></div><div style="">Best regards&nbsp;</div><div style=""><br></div><div style="">Tor&nbsp;</div><div style=""><div><br></div><div dir="ltr" data-smartmail="gmail_signature"><div dir="ltr"><div>Tor Del Federico</div><div>Principal</div></div></div></div><div><br>The British School Yangon<br></div></span></font></div></div><div style="text-align: left;"><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);" size="2">www.britishschoolyangon.org</font></p></div></div>]]></td>
